id: pm-tmhs
title: "GH-592: tracker_not_initialized recovery re-suggests pm init even when a --pm-path tracker exists — following it silently splits workspace state"
description: "GitHub issue #592 (GH-501 residue): a workspace initialized with --pm-path <custom> still fails bare commands with tracker_not_initialized, and the recovery bundle re-suggests pm init — creating a second tracker at <cwd>/.agents/pm and silently splitting workspace state. Fix = recovery bundle documents that discovery probes .agents/pm only and names --pm-path/PM_PATH; ideally detects an existing non-default tracker nearby (e.g. <cwd>/.pm or one level down) and suggests the exact --pm-path invocation instead of init. Capability-aware hint-rendering family (pm-qljv class)."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: agent-ux,init,recovery-hints
created_at: "2026-07-18T10:08:48.018Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-18T12:15:02.285Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-18T12:14:11.361Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 150
acceptance_criteria: tracker_not_initialized recovery names --pm-path/PM_PATH and the .agents/pm-only discovery rule; nearby non-default tracker detection suggests the concrete --pm-path command instead of pm init; no false-positive suggestions from unrelated settings.json files; regression coverage including the GH-501 positional-init fixed path
parent: pm-mpbb
risk: medium
confidence: high
resolution: fixed
expected_result: "When a nearby custom tracker exists, unconfigured commands suggest its exact --pm-path and PM_PATH selection instead of recommending a second tracker initialization."
actual_result: "Recovery formatting discovers valid directly nested custom roots, excludes common dependency/build/VCS directories, and emits exact selection commands; otherwise it accurately explains supported discovery."
